knife bootstrap

A bootstrap is a process that installs Chef on a target system so that it can run as a chef-client and communicate with a Chef server.
http://docs.opscode.com/knife_bootstrap.html
Neesd the IP address of the node:
knife bootstrap IP_ADDRESS

Could use 
(1a) JCloud to create VMs or
(1b) Knife to create VMs
(2)  then use knife to install Chef-Client
(3)  then use knife to install chef roles on nodes